  "description": {
    "overview": "Adversaries may abuse mmc.exe to proxy execution of malicious .msc files. Microsoft Management Console (MMC) is a binary that may be signed by Microsoft and is used in several ways in either its GUI or in a command prompt. MMC can be used to create, open, and save custom consoles that contain administrative tools created by Microsoft, called snap-ins. These snap-ins may be used to manage Windows systems locally or remotely. MMC can also be used to open Microsoft created .msc files to manage system configuration.",
    "examples": [
      {
        "example": "mmc C:\\Users\\foo\\admintools.msc /a",
        "description": "Open a custom, saved console msc file in author mode."
      },
      {
        "example": "mmc gpedit.msc",
        "description": "Open the Group Policy Editor application window."
      },
      {
        "example": "mmc wbadmin.msc delete catalog -quiet",
        "description": "Deletes the backup catalog on the system without prompts to the user."
      },
      {
        "example": "mmc.exe -Embedding C:\\path\\to\\test.msc",
        "description": "Invoke the malicious CLSID payload."
      }
    ],
